Those who know me are aware of my history of skincare cancer and my passion for educating others on it.

There are so many people who know very little about it. You can get it anywhere on your body, even your eyes 👀 

Everyone should get 1 full-body skin check by a dermatologist every single year. 

If you don’t, please start! It is such a silent killer and so easily preventable. It is also easily treatable if caught early.

H A P P I N E S S

Most people associate happiness with external sources. Whether it is the relationships we have, the success we achieve, material items we possess; we somehow believe those are the places we find happiness.

And this is exactly why so many people seem to never find it. TRUE happiness is not something that can be physically taken away from you. It’s something you dig deep inside yourself to find. It’s something you always have, regardless of what is going on outside of you.

I have fought hard in life to find inner happiness and I’m here to tell you it is NOT easy. Society has taught us all how to find temporary comfort, emotional bandaids. But what we all really need to learn is self healing, self acceptance, and self love.

I don’t care how much money you have, how successful you are, or all the possessions you own - you will never be genuinely happy until you put in that emotional work.

With that said, here are some small habits you can start today in your pursuit of happiness:

✍️ Start journaling. Get all of your thoughts and feelings out.
🚫Take a break from social media. It is often more toxic than anything.
🏋🏻‍♀️Exercise. Never underestimate the power of endorphins.
🧘🏻‍♀️Meditate. This will teach you to start looking more within yourself.

I’ve recently been adding swimming to my workout regimen, and for several good reasons. 💦 
As if the benefits listed weren’t enough, one of my favorite parts about swimming is that you can push yourself a bit harder because you don’t get overheated. 
It’s also much easier on the joints and serves as a great active recovery exercise. Studies have actually shown that doing a moderate workout in the pool on recovery days can enable you to workout longer than those who take it easy on recovery days.
